keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher for a trip related to the U.S. v. Epstein case (docket 2018R01618).
The trip's purpose was 'Witness Interviews' and took place from November 13-15, 2019 in Santa Monica, CA.
The voucher total expenses were $967.45 against an estimated trip cost of $1,219.95.
The email was sent from a travel services provider to a Department of Justice email address, indicating official government travel.
The document shows ongoing investigative activity (witness interviews) in the Epstein case as of late 2019.
